  "prompt": "How much time does a waiter spend in taking orders?",
  "response": "The amount of time a waiter spends taking orders can vary widely depending on several factors, such as the type of restaurant, the complexity of the menu, the size of the party, and the efficiency of the waiter. On average, taking orders might take anywhere from a few minutes to ten minutes per table. \n\nFor a small party at a casual dining restaurant, it might only take a couple of minutes. For larger parties or more upscale establishments where guests might have more questions about the menu, wine pairings, or special requests, it could take longer. Additionally, if the restaurant uses technology like tablets for ordering, this process might be quicker.\n\nTo give a rough estimate, a waiter might spend approximately 3-10 minutes per table taking orders in a typical dining scenario.",
